name: Skai Jackson
summary: Former Disney Channel actress Skai Jackson was arrested on suspicion of domestic battery following an altercation with her boyfriend at Universal Studios. Universal Studios security intervened and detained Jackson, who was later arrested by the Los Angeles Police Department. Jackson was booked and released on bail. The Los Angeles Times reports that the alleged victim, Jackson's boyfriend, suffered minor injuries. Jackson has not publicly commented on the arrest.

name: J.J. McCarthy
summary: Minnesota Vikings rookie quarterback J.J. McCarthy is set to undergo knee surgery after suffering a meniscus tear, which will sideline him indefinitely. The injury occurred during a training camp practice, leaving the Vikings' backup quarterback position uncertain for their second preseason game. McCarthy had been impressing coaches and fans during training camp, leading many to question the starting position of veteran quarterback Kirk Cousins. The Vikings will now need to assess their options for a backup quarterback, with Nick Mullens and Kellen Mond as the most likely candidates. McCarthy's injury is a setback for the Vikings, who were hoping to have a strong backup quarterback behind Cousins.

name: Starbucks stock
summary: Starbucks is experiencing significant changes, including an activist investor, Starboard Value, acquiring a stake in the company. In response, Starbucks announced the poaching of Chipotle's CEO, Brian Niccol, as its new chief executive. This move has sent Starbucks' stock soaring, while Chipotle's stock has declined. Interim CEO Howard Schultz has sold a portion of his stock, raising questions about the company's future. Analysts speculate that Starbucks' stock could potentially double under Niccol's leadership. However, some concerns linger regarding the company's overall health, including its reliance on pumpkin spice lattes and challenges in the retail sector.

name: Tropical Storm Ernesto
summary: Tropical Storm Ernesto, expected to strengthen into a hurricane, is currently churning across the Caribbean. Puerto Rico has canceled classes and activated the National Guard as the storm approaches. Ernesto has already passed over several islands, and forecasters predict it will continue to intensify. Hurricane Watches have been issued as the storm progresses towards the US. Maps showing the storm's path indicate it may hit Puerto Rico, bringing heavy rain and flooding. However, Louisiana is not expected to be impacted.
